Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @British Chicken Thighs{4}, 
@Peri Peri Seasoning{1%sachet} and a drizzle of @oil{}. Season and toss to coat.

Lay the chicken thighs flat onto a lined #baking tray{}. Once hot, roast on the
middle shelf of your oven until browned and cooked through, ~{16-18%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

When the chicken has cooked for ~{6%minutes}, add the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g}
to the tray. Drizzle with oil and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast for
the remaining ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken.

Pour the boiled water into a #large saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.
Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{}, then pop it on top of the pan and allow to
steam.

Meanwhile, drain the @Sweetcorn{160%g} in a sieve.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the
heat if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn
to pick up some nice colour. Once cooked, transfer the corn to a #small bowl{}
and wipe the pan clean.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Cloves{2} (or use a garlic press). Halve,
peel and chop the @Onion{1} into small pieces.

Pop the pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Add the onion to the pan and fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the @Tomato Puree{30%g}, garlic and @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}.
Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Return the charred corn to the pan.

Pour in the @Chicken Stock Paste{15%g}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{100%ml} for the
sauce. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}.

When the rice is cooked, add to the #frying pan{} along with the @Butter{20%g}.
Stir to combine, then remove from the heat.

Taste the rice and season with salt and pepper if needed.

When the chicken is cooked, drizzle over the @Honey{1%tbsp} and turn to coat
evenly.

When everything's ready, share your charred corn rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the chicken thighs and Tenderstem® Broccoli.

Finish by drizzling the @Low Fat Natural Yoghurt{75%g} over. Enjoy!